1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2178, Page 1, Section A, Line 3, by
2 inserting after all of said section and line the following:
3
4 "115.240. The election authority for any political subdivision or special district shall
5 label ballot measures relating to property taxation that are submitted by such political
6 subdivision or special district to a vote of the people numerically or alphabetically only. No such
7 ballot measure shall be labeled in a descriptive manner aside from its numerical or alphabetical
8 designation.
9 115.706. 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no ballot
10 measure proposing the imposition, increase, or extension of an ad valorem property tax by a
11 political subdivision shall be deemed approved unless a majority of the votes cast on the
12 question are in favor; and
13 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, beginning on January 1,
14 2027, the ballot language for a question submitted to voters by a political subdivision desiring to
15 levy a real property tax or personal property tax shall include at least the following elements, as
16 applicable:
17 (1) The name of the political subdivision imposing the property tax;
18 (2) The real property or personal property on which the property tax will be imposed;
19 (3) The current tax rate ceiling, the proposed tax rate ceiling, and, if the political
20 subdivision is seeking authorization to increase an existing tax, the difference between the
21 proposed new tax rate ceiling and the current tax rate ceiling, expressed in percentage changed
22 and the number of cents per one hundred dollars of assessed valuation. The percentage change
23 shall be calculated by subtracting the current tax rate ceiling from the proposed tax rate ceiling,
24 dividing the result by the current tax rate ceiling, and multiplying the quotient by one hundred;
25 (4) The length of time for which the tax will be imposed or the expiration date of the tax;
26 (5) The purpose for which the tax will be imposed;
27 (6) A description of additional actions a political subdivision affected by the ballot issue
28 will be required to take;
29 (7) If the political subdivision is seeking authorization to issue bonds, notes, or other
30 obligations:
Action Taken___________________________________________ Date __________________
