1 (a) An indication that bonds, notes, or other obligations will be issued if the proposal is
2 approved;
3 (b) The kind of bonds, notes, or other obligations that will be issued including, but not
4 limited to, general obligation bonds or revenue bonds; and
5 (c) The total amount of such bonds, notes, or other obligations;
6 (8) A disclosure that an increase to a tax rate ceiling could result in a tax rate increase;
7 (9) A statement indicating the real property or personal property that will be affected by
8 such tax or tax rate ceiling increase, containing wording substantially similar to the following, as
9 applicable:
"If approved, this proposition could increase the property taxes of:
A residential property ______ (insert levy amount multiplied by
100,000 multiplied by 0.0019) per $100,000 of appraised valuation;
A commercial property ______ (insert levy amount multiplied by
100,000 multiplied by 0.0032) per $100,000 of appraised valuation;
An agricultural property ______ (insert levy amount multiplied by
100,000 multiplied by 0.0012) per $100,000 of appraised valuation;
A motor vehicle ______ (insert levy amount multiplied by 10,000
multiplied by 0.00333) per $10,000 of appraised valuation."
10 3. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no polical subdivision or
11 election authority shall advertise or describe any proposed tax on property in a political
12 subdivision as not increasing taxes, or any language to that effect, unless both:
13 (1) Failing to adopt the proposed measure would cause an actual increase in the tax rate;
14 and
15 (2) Adopting the proposed measure would cause the tax rate to stay the same or
16 decrease.
17 4. The ballot language statements shall fairly and accurately explain what a vote for and
18 what a vote against the measure represent. The ballot language shall be true and impartial
19 statements of the effect of a vote for and against the measure in language neither intentionally
20 argumentative nor likely to create prejudice for or against the proposed measure."; and
21
22 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
23 accordingly.
